Get-vCloud

Get-vCloud is a Powershell function library for VMware's vCloud API.


Installation

1. Download the .ps1 (or zip file) from GitHub and place in the folder of your choice.
2. Import the functions using "dot-sourcing" like so:

	. .\vcloud-functions.ps1

3. Profit!


The Functions

Current "cmdlets" are:

Connect-vCloud
Delete-vCloudURI
Deploy-vCloudvApp
Disconnect-vCloud
Get-vCloudCatalog
Get-vCloudConsole
Get-vCloudMedia
Get-vCloudNetwork
Get-vCloudOrg
Get-vCloudURI
Get-vCloudvApp
Get-vCloudvAppTemplate
Get-vCloudvDC
Get-vCloudVM
Post-vCloudURI
PowerOff-vCloudvApp
PowerOff-vCloudVM
PowerOn-vCloudvApp
PowerOn-vCloudVM
Undeploy-vCloudvApp


HELP!

For help on using the functions:

	get-help <cmdlet>
